// EXPECT_COMPILE_ERROR [E_INFINITE_TYPE]
//
// Q-infinite-value-type (D280 §4) — NEGATIVE: a direct VALUE self-reference.
//
//     type N value { next N }
//
// A `value` record is laid out INLINE wherever it appears as a field
// (`NovaValue_N`), with NO pointer indirection. So `N` containing a field of
// type `N` by value is GENUINELY INFINITE — the layout recurses `N` → `next: N`
// → `N` → … without bound; there is no finite object size.
//
// The dedicated detector (`check_infinite_type` in types/mod.rs) walks the
// INLINE-containment graph and finds the back-edge `N → next → N`, emitting a
// clear `E_INFINITE_TYPE` AT TYPE-CHECK TIME (no `size_of` needed to surface
// it). The message names the type (`N`) + the offending field (`next`) and
// suggests boxing via sum / Option / `*N` / `[]N`.
//
// INTENT: `nova check` EXITS NONZERO with `E_INFINITE_TYPE` on the bare decl.

module plan144_inftype.neg_direct_self

// Genuinely-infinite value self-cycle (no boxing). Reported at check time.
type N value { next N }
